1558278.title: 400 East 59th Street - First Avenue

707642f-a.text:
(1)
First avenue, east side, north from 59th Street; seen through
the arch of the Queensboro Bridge approach.
A boy is stealing a ride on a north-bound street car of the
Second Avenue line. At the time of this picture, this line
is about to be discontinued and replaced by bus service.
March 5, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, showing a south-bound street car.
March 5, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

713992f-a.text:
59th Street, west from First Avenue. In the background are the hotels Delmonico and Sherry-Netherland, in a direct line with the camera, so that they seem to be one building, and to the
left, the Hotel Pierre.
March S, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
